# PHP CS Fixer required

Never leave PHP changes that fail `php-cs-fixer`. GitHub CI runs `composer check` → `check-style` (dry-run) and fails the job on any diff.

## After editing PHP under `src/` or `tests/`

1. Run fixer on the touched files (preferred) or the project check:
   - `php vendor/friendsofphp/php-cs-fixer/php-cs-fixer fix --config=.php-cs-fixer.php --path-mode=override -- path/to/File.php`
   - or `composer check-style` / full `composer check` before finishing
2. If dry-run reports a diff, apply the fix (same command without `--dry-run`) and re-check.
3. Do not consider the task done while style check would fail.

## Project conventions the fixer enforces (common pitfalls)

- `fully_qualified_strict_types` with `import_symbols`: prefer imported short class names in PHPDoc `@see` / types, not `\ON\Data\...` FQCNs — add `use` imports instead.
- Tabs for indent, LF line endings.
- Ordered imports, no unused imports.

Config: `.php-cs-fixer.php`.
